                <h5 class="text-primary mb-4">Community Standards</h5>

                <!-- Posting Guidelines -->
                <div class="card mb-4 border-primary">
                    <div class="card-header bg-light">
                        <h6 class="mb-0 text-primary">
                            <i class="fas fa-edit me-2"></i>Posting Guidelines
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h6 class="text-success">Do:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Be Respectful:</strong> Treat all community members with courtesy and respect</li>
                            <li><strong>Stay On Topic:</strong> Focus discussions on alley trash management, neighborhood cleanup, and community improvement</li>
                            <li><strong>Share Constructive Ideas:</strong> Offer practical suggestions and solutions</li>
                            <li><strong>Use Appropriate Categories:</strong> Choose the right category for your posts (general, cleanup, issue, announcement)</li>
                            <li><strong>Include Relevant Details:</strong> Provide specific information about locations, issues, and proposed solutions</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h6 class="text-danger">Don't:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Personal Attacks:</strong> No name-calling, harassment, or personal criticism</li>
                            <li><strong>Off-Topic Content:</strong> Avoid political debates, commercial advertising, or unrelated topics</li>
                            <li><strong>Spam or Repetitive Posts:</strong> Don't post the same content multiple times</li>
                            <li><strong>Inappropriate Language:</strong> Keep language family-friendly and professional</li>
                            <li><strong>False Information:</strong> Verify facts before posting, especially about city policies</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Alley Trash Best Practices -->
                <div class="card mb-4 border-success">
                    <div class="card-header bg-light">
                        <h6 class="mb-0 text-success">
                            <i class="fas fa-recycle me-2"></i>Alley Trash Management Best Practices
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h6 class="text-success">Proper Trash Placement:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Container Placement:</strong> Place trash containers at least 3 feet from walls and fences</li>
                            <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Ensure collection vehicles can easily access your containers</li>
                            <li><strong>Container Condition:</strong> Use sturdy, lidded containers to prevent spills and animal access</li>
                            <li><strong>Overflow Prevention:</strong> Don't overfill containers or leave bags outside containers</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h6 class="text-success">Recycling Guidelines:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Separate Recyclables:</strong> Use designated recycling containers for paper, plastic, metal, and glass</li>
                            <li><strong>Clean Materials:</strong> Rinse containers before recycling</li>
                            <li><strong>Check Local Rules:</strong> Verify what materials are accepted in your area</li>
                            <li><strong>Reduce Waste:</strong> Consider composting food waste and yard debris</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h6 class="text-success">Neighborhood Cooperation:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Discuss trash collection schedules with neighbors</li>
                            <li><strong>Shared Spaces:</strong> Coordinate with neighbors on shared alley maintenance</li>
                            <li><strong>Problem Reporting:</strong> Report missed pickups or service issues promptly</li>
                            <li><strong>Community Cleanup:</strong> Participate in neighborhood cleanup events</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Safety Guidelines -->
                <div class="card mb-4 border-warning">
                    <div class="card-header bg-light">
                        <h6 class="mb-0 text-warning">
                            <i class="fas fa-shield-alt me-2"></i>Safety Guidelines
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h6 class="text-success">Personal Safety:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Visibility:</strong> Wear bright clothing when working in alleys</li>
                            <li><strong>Proper Equipment:</strong> Use gloves, sturdy shoes, and appropriate tools</li>
                            <li><strong>Weather Awareness:</strong> Avoid working in extreme weather conditions</li>
                            <li><strong>Buddy System:</strong> Work with others when possible, especially in isolated areas</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h6 class="text-success">Hazard Awareness:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Sharp Objects:</strong> Be careful with broken glass, metal, or other sharp materials</li>
                            <li><strong>Chemical Safety:</strong> Don't handle unknown chemicals or hazardous materials</li>
                            <li><strong>Animal Safety:</strong> Be aware of wildlife and stray animals in alley areas</li>
                            <li><strong>Vehicle Traffic:</strong> Watch for delivery vehicles and maintenance trucks</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h6 class="text-danger">Emergency Contacts:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Police:</strong> 911 for emergencies, non-emergency line for other issues</li>
                            <li><strong>Sanitation Department:</strong> Report missed pickups and service problems</li>
                            <li><strong>Code Enforcement:</strong> Report violations and safety hazards</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Community Engagement -->
                <div class="card mb-4 border-info">
                    <div class="card-header bg-light">
                        <h6 class="mb-0 text-info">
                            <i class="fas fa-users me-2"></i>Community Engagement
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h6 class="text-success">Getting Involved:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Join Discussions:</strong> Participate in community posts and share your experiences</li>
                            <li><strong>Share Success Stories:</strong> Post about successful cleanup efforts and improvements</li>
                            <li><strong>Organize Events:</strong> Coordinate neighborhood cleanup days</li>
                            <li><strong>Mentor New Members:</strong> Help new community members learn best practices</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h6 class="text-success">Effective Communication:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Be Specific:</strong> Include details about locations, times, and specific issues</li>
                            <li><strong>Use Photos:</strong> Share before/after photos when appropriate (respecting privacy)</li>
                            <li><strong>Follow Up:</strong> Update posts with outcomes and resolutions</li>
                            <li><strong>Stay Positive:</strong> Focus on solutions rather than just problems</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Moderation Policy -->
                <div class="card mb-4 border-danger">
                    <div class="card-header bg-light">
                        <h6 class="mb-0 text-danger">
                            <i class="fas fa-gavel me-2"></i>Moderation Policy
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h6 class="text-success">Our Approach:</h6>
                        <p>We believe in fostering a self-regulating community where members help maintain positive standards. 
                        However, we reserve the right to moderate content that violates these guidelines.</p>

                        <h6 class="text-warning">Actions We May Take:</h6>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Warning:</strong> First-time violations may result in a private warning</li>
                            <li><strong>Content Removal:</strong> Posts that violate guidelines may be removed</li>
                            <li><strong>Temporary Suspension:</strong> Repeated violations may result in temporary account suspension</li>
                            <li><strong>Permanent Ban:</strong> Severe or repeated violations may result in permanent account removal</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h6 class="text-info">Appeals Process:</h6>
                        <p>If you believe content was removed in error, you may contact the moderation team through the contact form. 
                        We review all appeals fairly and promptly.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

